em><title>Breakdown</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/breakdown</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/breakdown</guid></item><item><title>A theory for everything</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/theory_for_everything</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/theory_for_everything</guid></item><item><title>Principles Index</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles</guid></item><item><title>Teaching and Learning</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/teaching_learning</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/teaching_learning</guid></item><item><title>Stress system</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/stress_system</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/stress_system</guid></item><item><title>Development</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/development</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/development</guid></item><item><title>Bad Emotions</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/bad_emotions</link><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/Practice/principles/bad_emotions</guid></item><item><title>explorer</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/explorer</link><description>Knowledge Guardian.Looking for knowledge and new things to conquer, new technology, new techniques, 'I can conquer everything, but feel never satisfied'. The Explorer path is an invitation to keep our curiosity for novelty, for new tecniques and solutions, and to not stop looking for something better.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/explorer</guid></item><item><title>sage</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/sage</link><description>Spirit Guardian. Concepts and categories are the path, 'I can understand everything but never feel close to it'. The Sage path invite us to analyse things in their components and to create more encompasing models that help us clarify our minds and the big problems of existence.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/sage</guid></item><item><title>carer</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/carer</link><description>Life Guardian. Connecting with even the smallest thing, 'I can care for everything, but never for myself'. The Carer path is an invitation towards closeness to otherness, by an appreciation of life and the movements of nature.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/carer</guid></item><item><title>dreamer</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/dreamer</link><description>Soul Guardian. Allows imagination and fantasy to guide the path:,'I can become everything, but never have a hold of it'. The Dreamer path is an invitation towards the magic of poetry, metaphor, art, and daydreaming. People in this path feels deeply and believes dream brings deeper truths.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/path/dreamer</guid></item><item><title>warrior</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/warrior</link><description>Striking and rigorous. Warriors want to keep developing so they can achieve the next stage, to become more powerful and efficient. The Warrior has a self development approach, aiming to help by becoming stronger, achieving higher concepts and techniques.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/warrior</guid></item><item><title>artist</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/artist</link><description>Feeling everything deeply. Artists express their connection with things and intense places. Artists become more themselves as they feel more. The Artist has a self deepening approach, focussing more in their own feelings and experiences, aiming to explore the deepths of the soul.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/artist</guid></item><item><title>lider/group</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/lider</link><description>Belonging and shared identity. Tendencty to merge as a whole for a common vision with a leader who maintains the spirit and the coherence of the group. The Leader has a group approach where they want to find an inspiration that may take them and others to a better place.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/lider</guid></item><item><title>coach/team</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/coach</link><description>Focused on the strategy and a target.Teams are differentiatied and the coach can be a strategist who plans how to use all the talents to achieve a goal. The Coach position works with a team, and aims for its perfecting by following clear techniques and strategies.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/ind_trad/coach</guid></item><item><title>playful</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/playful</link><description>Proposes and accepts. A type of therapist who tries to bring new things to the session to help the client process and move forward. They see many opportunities to help through little exercises like art-making, meditation, and role-playing. The goal is to activate the client's own processes by creating spaces of insight. The Playful position invite us to create activities that can mobilise emotions, so we can process them.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/playful</guid></item><item><title>changer</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/changer</link><description>Proposes and challenges. The type of therapist who wants to promote change in the client by bringing exercises, homework, and a battery of solutions. They have an answer for everything and a tool for every problem. They are on top of what is happening and will try to help you feel better soon. They tend to be pragmatic, enthusiastic, and encouraging. The Changer position invite us to encurage change in our clients by directly finding solutions, new behaviours, or exercises.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/changer</guid></item><item><title>compassionate</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/compassionate</link><description>Follows and accepts. Type of therapist that welcomes and holds anything that the client brings. Its words and interventions are soft and give a feeling of wholesomness. They never make you feel uncomfortable, nor challenge any of your comments. They are patient and no mater what you do, always see it in a good light. The Compassionate position make us feel close to other's feelings and suffering, giving lots of space to express other people's experience. In this position we follow the rhytm of the other person avoiging interruptions</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/compassionate</guid></item><item><title>inquisitive</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/inquisitive</link><description>Follows and challenges.This type of therapist follows the client's process silently and awaits the right moment to comment or say a few words. They work by finding details in what the client brings that may trigger internal processes. They are subtle and make you feel they know something you have yet to figure out. The Inquisitive position invite us to analyse and collect information to find clues of deeper conflicts and underlying dynamics.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/positions/inquisitive</guid></item><item><title>Spiritual</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/spiritual</link><description>The world is mysterious and that is beautiful. Awe, compassion, intention are important parts of human experience. The spiritual philosophy searches for the harmony that leads to the expression of our deepest self. We create the conditions, but are the deeper forces which need to act.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/spiritual</guid></item><item><title>Scientific</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/scientific</link><description>The world can be studied by trials and statistics. An impartial observer tries to clean itself from distortions and emotions to reach a pure access to reality. We need to focus on what can be predictable and controllable, and leave behind knowledge that does not fit with this assumptions. It encompasses positivism and post-positivism.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/scientific</guid></item><item><title>Phenomenology</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/phenomenology</link><description>Experience is the deepest truth we can access as we are experiential beings. We need to develop methods to acknowledge our prejudices and how they affect what we experience. From Husserl, Heidegger and Merlou Ponty, this tradition has strong foundation in philosophy.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/phenomenology</guid></item><item><title>Hermeneutic</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/hermeneutics</link><description>Symbols, behaviors, practices, thoughts, they all have deeper truths if we take the time to investigate. We are part of the investigation, as symbols require our own process of extending our horizons of meaning and challenging our pre-conceptions.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/hermeneutics</guid></item><item><title>Constructive</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/constructive</link><description>Reality is build, it is a construction that emerges by language, biology and culture. We need to study those constructions at the individual and also the social levels. We do not aim to have one truth, but one for each construction we are researching. It includes constructivism and socio-constructionism.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/constructive</guid></item><item><title>Cybernetic</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/cybernetic</link><description>The world is made of processes and patterns, that we can model and intervene. There is not need for deep abstractions or associations when we can see what is actually happening and describe it formally. Computers are a type of system, and families are another. We can use similar methods, and see the world as information. G Bateson was one of the first ones to use these methods in a psychological research.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/cybernetic</guid></item><item><title>Participatory</title><link>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/participatory</link><description>We are part of what we study and we need to own it. Reality is unique for each, but at the same time there is a common reality we are all accessing in our participation with it. Our methods cannot separate action and knowledge.</description><pubDate>Tue, 30 Jul 2024 20:20:01 +0100</pubDate><guid>https://crea-theory-static.vercel.app/pages/philosophies/participatory</guid></item></channel></rss>